# kbs recognition + teaching rules. Pipe-delimited; fields are whitespace-trimmed.
# Column 1 is the record kind. '*' or empty = match anything. First matching rule wins.
#
# rule    | type | key            | target          | macro      | source | action
# bykey   | source | key          | action
# synth   | source | key          | action
# builtin | key  | action
# example | source | text
#
# type: x=shell-cmd c=command s=macro f=widget/function   key: canonical (Ctrl-R, Up, ...)
# target/macro: substring tested against the binding's target.  action '@bykey' -> bykey table.

# --- fzf ---
rule    | *    | *              | fzf-file-widget | *          | fzf    | Pick file(s); insert path at cursor
rule    | *    | *              | __fzf_cd__      | *          | fzf    | cd into a chosen sub-directory
rule    | *    | *              | __fzf_history__ | *          | fzf    | Search shell history (fzf)
rule    | *    | *              | fzf             | *          | fzf    |

# --- atuin (recognised by its private \C-x\C-_A dispatch macro signature) ---
rule    | s    | *              | *               | \C-x\C-_A  | atuin  | @bykey
rule    | *    | *              | __atuin         | *          | atuin  | @bykey
bykey   | atuin | Ctrl-R        | History search (fuzzy, synced across machines)
bykey   | atuin | Up            | History up-search by prefix

# --- ble.sh / shell ---
rule    | *    | Ctrl-Z         | fg              | *          | ble.sh | Resume the most recent suspended job (fg)
rule    | *    | *              | complete        | *          | ble.sh | Trigger completion
rule    | *    | *              | menu-complete   | *          | ble.sh | Menu completion (cycle candidates)

# --- synthetic rows (not keymap bindings) ---
synth   | fzf  | {trigger}<Tab> | Fuzzy-completion trigger

# --- level-B built-in keys (presence here = part of the level-B allowlist) ---
builtin | Tab            | Complete
builtin | Up             | Previous line / history
builtin | Down           | Next line / history
builtin | Left           | Move cursor left
builtin | Right          | Move cursor right (or accept autosuggestion at line end)
builtin | Home           | Start of line
builtin | End            | End of line (or accept autosuggestion)
builtin | Ctrl-A         | Start of line
builtin | Ctrl-E         | End of line
builtin | Ctrl-K         | Kill to end of line
builtin | Ctrl-U         | Kill to start of line
builtin | Ctrl-W         | Kill previous word
builtin | Ctrl-Y         | Yank (paste) killed text
builtin | Ctrl-L         | Clear screen

# --- teaching examples (footer) ---
example | fzf  | vim **<Tab>      fuzzy-pick a file to edit
example | fzf  | cd **<Tab>       fuzzy-pick a sub-directory
example | fzf  | ssh **<Tab>      fuzzy-pick a host
example | fzf  | kill -9 **<Tab>  fuzzy-pick a process by PID
example | atuin | Ctrl-R          search synced history; type to filter, Enter to run
